events.name: Front End TL;DR
events.description: Have you ever come across something new in front end, had the browser tab open for weeks, but never found time to research it? Use this event as an excuse to dig a little deeper. Front End TL;DR is a learning event where everyone participates. Helps to bring a laptop. For the August meetup we will visit Wego, a travel search site headquartered in Singapore. Join to level-up your front-end knowledge, meet other front-end developers, or learn how the engineers at Wego ship code. 7:00pm — Arrival, seating, food & drinks7:15pm — Intro talk by the host7:30pm — R&D: random team assignment, choose a topic, learn something new9:00pm — Q&A: share what your team learned9:30pm — The end. There will be guest wifi, food & drinks provided. Address: WegoShaw Tower 100 Beach Road #23-07/13Singapore 189702 Every third Monday of the month. Different venue each time. More info: http://feds.strikingly.com/
